acqinfo.p: On September 25, 2002, Ms. Sara Revis donated archival papers from the Burleith Garden to The George Washington University Gelman Library.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Burleith Garden Club began on October 18, 1949 with fourteen members attending the first meeting. In 1950, the club decided to join the Burleith Citizens Association, but became independent again in 1954. The Burleith Garden Club is one of the charter members of the National Capital Garden Club League.

The Burleith Garden Club activities included speakers at the monthly meetings, and landscaping work in the community. For example, at one point, the club collected funds from homeowners to protect the Burleith community from Japanese beetles. The areas covered by the Japanese beetle program included private homes, parks, and school property. In addition, members participated in the flower show held at the National Guard Armory serving as judges, hostesses, and entrants. The club held garden tours in the spring and provided flowers and plants to shut-ins and the elderly during Christmas and Easter. At the April 2000 meeting, in response to declining membership, the club endorsed a proposal to become a standing committee of the Burleith Citizens Association.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection contains bylaws, annual reports, membership lists, lists of officers, flyers, correspondence, one stapled booklet "My Favorite Recipes", and the neighborhood tot lot and flower mart. The materials span the dates 1949-2000.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into three series: General files, Graphics, and Minutes.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains annual reports, and membership dues that help relay the story of the operational workings of the club. This series consists of a sample of the type of issues and topics important to the garden club. This includes organizations they associated with such as the Friends of the National Arboretum. The material dates from 1949-98.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of photographs and slides. These images represent Garden Club activities such as the flower mart, Hillwood, and a picnic. Some of the images relate to the work the club did for the Burleith neighborhood such as landscaping for the tot lot.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of club minutes. The records run from the first meeting in 1949 until its last meeting in 2000 when the club decided to transition into a committee within the Burleith Citizens Association.
